      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions must replicate VAD operating envelope including flow rates 2–6 L/min and rotational speeds 2400–3600 RPM with traceable measurement uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments cover 5 of the 5 target operating points; flow measurement uncertainty is characterized. Temperature control and blood analog viscosity characterization are partially documented. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metrics (e.g., NRMSE, validation uncertainty) must be computed against experimental hemolysis index measurements with statistical rigor.",
      "rationale": "NRMSE computed across 5 operating points yields 18% error; validation uncertainty budget is partially assembled but experimental hemolysis measurement uncertainty is not fully propagated. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
